article.headline: Kansas 71, UTEP 50
article.story:
LAWRENCE, Kan. (AP)-- Crystal Kemp scored 15 points and Aquanita
Burras had 14 to lead Kansas past Texas-El Paso 71-50 Sunday in the
title game of the Holiday Inn Jayhawk Classic.

Kansas (2-2) jumped out to a 15-3 lead and UTEP, which shot only
34 percent from the field for the game, could not respond.

Tamara Ransburg had 10 points for the Jayhawks, and Lauren
Ervin, who had eight points and eight rebounds, finished 10-for-10
from the floor in the tournament.

UTEP (2-2) was led by Vaida Zagurskyte with 12 points and
Charlene Phelps with 10.

Kemp was named the tournament's Most Valuable Player. Ervin,
Burras, Zagurskyte, Marta Dydek of UTEP and Crystal Kitt of Alabama
State were voted to the all-tournament team.

UTEP shot 4-of-26 from the field and trailed 40-13 at the half.
